    "number": 30279,
    "state": "open",
    "state_reason": null,
    "title": "docs: Wrong/outdated docs for `tr(KEY)` in doc/descriptors.md",
    "body": "Bitcoin Core uses BIP-386 for `tr(...)` descriptors, and in the case of `tr(KEY)`, the produced key is tweaked according to BIP-341: \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/85cda4e225b4d5fd7aff403f69d827f23f6afbbc/bip-0341.mediawiki?plain=1#L156\r\n\r\nIn the current descriptors.md, it is documented that `tr(KEY)` uses `KEY` as the internal key, with no further comment:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/a7bc9b76e73f04dfe4d6ba42033fe38659090e8b/doc/descriptors.md?plain=1#L82\r\n\r\nBy looking only at descriptors.md without knowledge or reference to BIP-386, one can interpret `tr(KEY)` to use `KEY` directly without tweaking.\r\n\r\nIdeally the docs should be expanded to reference BIP-386.",
    "user": {
      "login": "benma",
      "id": 1225267,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMjUyNjc=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1225267?v=4",
